    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n7755" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πόλις, πτόλις</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ιος, πόληος</span>, dat. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πόληι</span>, pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πόληες,
          πόλιες</span>, gen. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πολίων</span>, dat.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πολίεσσι</span>, acc. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πόλιας, πόληας</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">city</span>, the whole district
          and community; hence with the name in apposition (not gen.); or as a
          part, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄκρη πόλις</span>, ‘acropolis,’
          ‘citadel;’ see <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄστυ</span>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
